		<title>The Sting Technique: How to add the grease into your bass fills and grooves (L#191)</title>
		<link>http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/technique/sting-technique-add-grease-bass-fills-grooves-l191.html</link>
		<comments>http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/technique/sting-technique-add-grease-bass-fills-grooves-l191.html#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Fri, 01 Apr 2016 12:19:54 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Travis Moore]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Technique]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/?p=13731</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<p>=== Over the last few years of playing I've developed a sliding vibrato technique where I slide super fast between two frets... You'll most likely have heard me use it a LOT before, as it's one of those things that...</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/technique/sting-technique-add-grease-bass-fills-grooves-l191.html">The Sting Technique: How to add the grease into your bass fills and grooves (L#191)</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com">Online Bass Lessons</a>.</p>
]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/i1k0NBNz9jw" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p>
<p>===</p>
<p>Over the last few years of playing I've developed a sliding vibrato technique where I slide super fast between two frets...</p>
<p>You'll most likely have heard me use it a LOT before, as it's one of those things that makes me sound... well, like me.</p>
<p>In a nutshell you can use this technique to interject that "synth type vibe" into your bass fills, lines and grooves. But most players have difficulty with it because they're making one really simple mistake.</p>
<p>I get heaps of questions about it when speaking to students within the <a href="https://www.scottsbasslessons.com/bass-academy" target="_blank">Academy</a> and also see many bass players really struggling with it, so I thought it was about time to film a lesson for you focusing on this technique and how to get it into your playing...</p>
<p><strong>In this lesson you're going to learn:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>All about "the sting" vibrato technique</li>
<li>How to practice this technique so it get's fully integrated within your own playing</li>
<li>The common mistakes bass players make that stop them using it effectively</li>
</ul>
<p>As always, see you in the shed...</p>
<p>Scott :)</p>
