<p>===</p>
<p>In this lesson I’m going to show you one of the most common bad habits I see beginner and intermediate bass players suffering from...</p>
<p>I call it "the see-saw".</p>
<p>If you do suffer from this common bad habit, playing faster lines and riffs will be pretty much impossible... it'd be like trying to run with a ball and chain attached to your foot!</p>
<p><strong>In this lesson you’re going to learn:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Exactly what the "see-saw" is</li>
<li>Why it's impossible to play faster lines and grooves if you do suffer from it</li>
<li>A killer exercise that will help you gain much more fretting hand (and finger) control</li>
<li>And most importantly... how to fix this bad habit! ;)</li>
</ul>
<p>Hopefully you'll enjoy this lesson and start using this exercise straight away. If you dig it, share it with your bass buddies so they can get in on the action!</p>
<p>As always, see you in the shed…</p>
<p>Scott :)</p>
