		<title>Groove Harder With These 3 Deadly Dynamics Exercises (L#188)</title>
		<link>http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/technique/groove-harder-with-these-3-deadly-dynamics-exercises-l188.html</link>
		<comments>http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/technique/groove-harder-with-these-3-deadly-dynamics-exercises-l188.html#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Fri, 04 Mar 2016 07:27:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Travis Moore]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Technique]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/?p=13438</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<p>=== Have you ever heard two bass players playing the exact same riff - one guy sounds ok, but the other guy sounds AWESOME? They're both playing in time. Both are playing the exact same notes... but they sound drastically...</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/technique/groove-harder-with-these-3-deadly-dynamics-exercises-l188.html">Groove Harder With These 3 Deadly Dynamics Exercises (L#188)</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com">Online Bass Lessons</a>.</p>
]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/fa9jA08bYr4" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p>
<p>===</p>
<p>Have you ever heard two bass players playing the exact same riff - one guy sounds ok, but the other guy sounds AWESOME?</p>
<p>They're both playing in time. Both are playing the exact same notes... but they sound drastically different.</p>
<p>Well, a lot of this is down to what I like to refer to as "Micro-Dynamics".</p>
<p>I'm not talking about general dynamics within a song - i.e. play softly in the verse, and then louder in the chorus. I'm specifically talking about "micro-dynamics" within your bass lines, grooves and fills.</p>
<p>It's soooo easy to overlook these, or even worse not even know that they exist!</p>
<p>So, I thought it'd be cool to show you 3 great exercises I use with students to help them really master these and get them into their technique and bass playing.</p>
<p>As always, see you in the shed...</p>
<p>Scott :)</p>
<p>PS. I also wanna tell you about something EPIC that is happening in a few weeks time.</p>
<p>In a nutshell, we're going to be hosting the biggest online bass event in history - it's totally free, and I want you to be a part of it!</p>
<p>We're calling it <strong>"SBL Live 2016"</strong>.</p>
<p>There's going be online seminars with some of the best bass educators in the world, give-aways, competitions, and more... keep a look out for further details coming soon!</p>
